('112', '20', '1', '', '2020-01-18 13:18:04', '93', '2914', '92877cefadbd91872106dda6110e05a3c9880089', '{\"id\":20,\"asset_id\":116,\"title\":\"Liverpool won the Champions League, beating Tottenham\",\"alias\":\"liverpool-won-the-champions-league-beating-tottenham\",\"introtext\":\"<p>Liverpool defeated Tottenham in London and won the Champions League for the first time since 2005.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The final match of the two English clubs, held on Saturday at the Madrid stadium \\u201cMetropolitano\\u201d, ended with a victory for Liverpool with a score of 2:0. Goals were scored by Mohamed Salah (2nd minute, penalty) and Divock Origi (87th).<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Already in the first minute of the meeting, Tottenham defender Moussa Sissoko played a hand in his penalty area, and the chief referee Damir Skomina appointed an eleven-meter kick, which Salah realized. In the 87th minute, Origi hit the goal of Hugo Lloris, setting the final score in the match.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The game began with a minute of silence in memory of the former football team of Spain Jose Antonio Reyes, who died in an accident on Saturday morning.<\\/p>\",\"fulltext\":\"\",\"state\":1,\"catid\":\"8\",\"created\":\"2020-01-18 13:18:04\",\"created_by\":\"93\",\"created_by_alias\":\"\",\"modified\":\"2020-01-18 13:18:04\",\"modified_by\":null,\"checked_out\":null,\"checked_out_time\":null,\"publish_up\":\"2020-01-18 13:18:04\",\"publish_down\":\"0000-00-00 00:00:00\",\"images\":\"{\\\"image_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_intro\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_intro_caption\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"float_fulltext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_alt\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"image_fulltext_caption\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"urls\":\"{\\\"urla\\\":false,\\\"urlatext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targeta\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlb\\\":false,\\\"urlbtext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetb\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"urlc\\\":false,\\\"urlctext\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"targetc\\\":\\\"\\\"}\",\"attribs\":\"{\\\"article_layout\\\":\\\"\