('1', 'com_content.article', 'A Chinese company has created a robot cat', 'a-chinese-company-has-created-a-robot-cat', '<p>The international electronics show (CES) was held in Los Angeles, where a Chinese company presented a cat-robot that can be trained. Elephant Robotics created the new project.</p>\r\n<p>The MarsCat robot is completely autonomous and can be configured. It reacts to the touch and voice of the owner and responds to the given name. He can also play with various items.</p>\r\n<p>The authors of the project are sure that Allergy sufferers and busy people who do not have the opportunity to pay much attention to a live pet will appreciate the gadget. The robot is not yet available for sale, but on the companys website, it can be ordered for $ 700.</p>\r\n<p>MarsCat was the first Elephant Robotics product designed for home use. Founded in 2016, the company produces robots to perform functions in industrial enterprises.</p>', '1', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '1', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"images\\/2020\\/01\\/18\\/MarsCat-63.jpg\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":\"\"}', '0', '{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}', '93', '', '2020-01-18 09:22:01', '93', '2020-01-19 12:51:44', '*', '2020-01-18 09:22:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '17', '110', '{\"image_intro\":\"images\\/2020\\/01\\/18\\/MarsCat-63.jpg\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}', '{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}', '6', '11', '5', '', '', '8', '', '1'),
('2', 'com_content.article', 'DEAnsect  an elastic insect robot that can withstand a swatter', 'deansect-an-elastic-insect-robot-that-can-withstand-a-swatter', '<p>Research in the field of robotics is very important and useful, especially the development of miniature robots that together are able to perform fairly complex tasks, working in places of natural disasters, technological disasters, etc. To do this, such robots must be very reliable, and researchers from the Swiss Federal Polytechnic University of Lausanne (Swiss Ecole Polytechnique Federale de Lausanne, EPFL) seem to have managed to realize all this to the fullest. The elastic insect robot they created is able to recover from impacts and continue to fulfill the task assigned to it.</p>\r\n<p>The weight of the new insect robot does not exceed one gram, it is moved using polymer artificial muscles (dielectric elastomer actuators, DEA), which formed the basis of its name  DEAnsect.</p>', '1', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '1', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_page_title\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_image\":\"images\\/2020\\/01\\/18\\/robots-DEAnsect3.jpg\",\"helix_ultimate_article_format\":\"standard\",\"helix_ultimate_audio\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_gallery\":\"\",\"helix_ultimate_video\":