('7', 'com_content.article', 'US stocks lower at close in 2019', 'us-stocks-lower-at-close-in-2019', '<p>The US stock market closed Tuesday with a fall amid negative dynamics from the telecommunications, oil and gas and industrial sectors.</p>\r\n<p>At the close in NYSE, the Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 0.72%, the S&amp;P 500 index fell 0.61%, and the NASDAQ Composite index fell 0.56%.</p>\r\n<p>The best performers of the session on the Dow Jones were Walt Disney Company (NYSE: DIS), which rose 1.65% or 1.90 points to trade at 116.86 at the close. Coca-Cola Company (NYSE: KO) added 0.26% or 0.12 points to trade at 46.67. Paper McDonalds Corporation (NYSE: MCD) rose in price by 0.23 p. (0.12%), closing at 190.08.</p>\r\n<p>Biggest losers included Caterpillar Inc (NYSE: CAT), which lost 2.48% or 3.47 points to trade at 136.35 in late trade. Shares of Dow Inc (NYSE: DOW) were up 0.84% (1.54%) to close at 56.27, while Boeing Co (NYSE: BA) were down 5.48% (1.46). %) and completed trading at around 369.04.</p>\r\n<p>The best performers of the session on the S&amp;P 500 were Cerner Corporation (NASDAQ: CERN), which rose 10.30% to 62.97, Monster Beverage Corp (NASDAQ: MNST), which gained 3.05% , closing at 54.69, and Campbell Soup Company shares (NYSE: CPB), which rose 2.49%, ending the session at 39.49.</p>\r\n<p>The worst performers of the session were Pentair PLC (NYSE: PNR), which fell 13.54% to trade at 39.13. Under Armor Inc A (NYSE: UAA) lost 4.69% and ended the session at 20.72. Quotes Advanced Micro Devices Inc (NASDAQ: AMD) fell in price by 4.52% to around 27.24.</p>', '1', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '1', '{\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"info_block_show_title\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_associations\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date